    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have a mapping that adjusts the `:args` list and echoes it. The mapping supports both normal mode, and linewise visual mode. However, in linewise visual mode, if the output of `:args` only takes a single line of screen space, it will not be shown if `showmode` is set.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`repro.lua`:\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('v', 'gA', function()\n\tlocal l = vim.fn.mode() == 'V' and 'v' or '.'\n\tlocal line1, line2 = vim.fn.line(l), vim.fn.line('.')\n\tlocal from, to = math.min(line1, line2), math.max(line1, line2)\n\n\tlocal lines = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_lines(0, from, to+1, true)\n\n\tvim.cmd(\"%argdel\")\n\tvim.cmd.argadd({ args = lines })\n\tvim.cmd.args()\nend)\n```\n`foo.txt`:\n```\n00000000000000000000\n11111111111111111111\n22222222222222222222\n33333333333333333333\n44444444444444444444\n55555555555555555555\n66666666666666666666\n77777777777777777777\n```\n\n`nvim -u repro.lua foo.txt`\n\n`VGgA` -> select all lines, execute `gA` mapping\n\nObserve `:args` output and `Press Enter` prompt shown\n\n`ggV2jgA` -> select only two lines, execute `gA` mapping\n\nObserve nothing shown\n\nrepeat with `set noshowmode`, Observe `:args` output and `Press Enter` prompt shown.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:args` output always shown\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A (cannot port reproducer to VimL)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\ngithub stable release",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
